18.44	Ernst_Zundel	Ernst Zündel	Ernst Christof Friedrich Zündel (born April 24, 1939) is a German Holocaust denier and pamphleteer. He has been jailed several times in Canada for publishing literature which "is likely to incite hatred against an identifiable group" and for being a threat to national security, in the United States for overstaying his visa, and in Germany for charges of "inciting racial hatred." He lived in Canada from 1958 to 2000.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1b/Ernst_Zundel.jpg
